This paper deals with data structures for approximate membership queries, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper discusses the Bloom filter, which is a widely used data structure for this problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the false-positive probability of the Bloom filter, which is related to information theory, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the security implications of the Bloom filter, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of Bloom filters for dictionaries, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
